itemListElement.name: Private Waterfall Rappelling Tour + Photo Package!

name: Private Waterfall Rappelling Tour + Photo Package!
description:
Looking for an exciting and memorable adventure in the wild mountains just outside of Seattle? Join Wild Sky on a thrilling waterfall rappeling tour designed for beginners and vacationers alike.

Our experienced guides can pick-up up to 3 people in our air-conditioned 4x4 SUV and take you on a private tour customized to your group's abilities and preferences. 

With top-quality gear provided, including state-of-the-art SELAND canyoning wetsuits and safety equipment, you can relax and focus on the adventure ahead.

Rappel down breathtaking waterfalls, hike through stunning canyons, and practice downclimbing with expert guidance from our International Canyoning Academy certified Swiftwater Canyoning Guide. Your safety is our top priority, so you can enjoy the experience with peace of mind.

Discover some of the best and most remarkable swiftwater canyons in the region with Wild Sky. Join us for an unforgettable adventure just outside Seattle!

review.name: Awesome experience!
review.reviewBody: This was a fantastic experience. As a family of 5, with kids ages 13, 11, and 7 it was a perfect day of adventure. The guides were excellent. One of our kids had some difficulty suiting up and they handled it like champs. They were professional and loads of fun at the same time.  Our guides were constantly encouraging and building up our whole group, adapting the adventure to what each person was capable of.   We repelled, scrambled, floated, jumped and swung all through the canyon that seemed to be hidden in plain sight.  It was a day loaded with fun and memories.  Couldn't recommend them enough.

review.name: Private Waterfall Rappelling Tour
review.reviewBody: We booked last minute with Sam bc another company canceled me one day before the Tour.  Things happen for a reason and can't be more happy how this waterfall canyoneering tour turned out. Our guides were careful and safe and took us on a tour of a lifetime rapelling down over 7 waterfalls.  The views and experience were outstanding.  Our expectations were blown away.  If you want a fun and challenging experience, book this tour.

review.name: Family canyoning adventure
review.reviewBody:
We had a great time in this canyoning adventure together with our kids (12-16 years old). We ran a full day session, which was an intense but awesome way to explore the canyon and the beautiful landscape. 

Our guides were helpful, made sure everyone had fun and kept us all safe.

review.name: New Favorite Pastime!
review.reviewBody: I came into this experience with ZERO previous canyoneering knowledge, although I do have some experience as a climber. Sam & Austin were so friendly and knowledgeable. They helped me through every step of the way, and I walked away feeling like I had learned a ton and gained some new skills. I couldn‚Äôt stop smiling the whole day ‚Äî it was a blast! Completely unique way to get outside, enjoy the weather, and challenge yourself. Couldn‚Äôt have asked for better guides and can‚Äôt wait to do it again.

review.name: The Perfect Adventure
review.reviewBody: Our Guide Sam was a blast! Did this trip with my husband and two kids. Sam is very safety conscious. He is fun, but firm, and my kids loved it. The canyon was different than anything we have ever done, but with our guides we felt like pros!

itemListElement.name: Mount Rainier National Park tour from Seattle

name: Mount Rainier National Park tour from Seattle
description: Embark on a journey from Seattle to the majestic Mount Rainier National Park. Begin your day with enlightening insights about the region from your guide as you travel. At Longmire Museum, immerse yourself in Rainier‚Äôs rich history, then marvel at the breathtaking beauty of Christine Falls, capturing the classic view of Mount Rainier. Feel nature‚Äôs might as you approach the towering Narada Falls via the Nisqually River. Experience ‚ÄòParadise,‚Äô where alpine meadows are your window to spotting diverse wildlife. Embrace the chance for a snowshoe expedition or sled down pristine terrains, conditions permitting. Alternatively, bask in the sublime beauty of Reflection Lake, a perfect mirror to Mount Rainier‚Äôs grandeur. Conclude your tour by acquainting yourself with Rainier‚Äôs tales at the visitor center before a comfortable ride back to Seattle.
